/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-scaled.jpg 1681w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-728x953.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-768x1005.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-1174x1536.jpg 1174w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-1565x2048.jpg 1565w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-150x196.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1681px) 100vw, 1681px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201681%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-scaled.jpg 1681w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-728x953.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-768x1005.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-1174x1536.jpg 1174w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-1565x2048.jpg 1565w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-150x196.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-2-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eYou could also toss something extra with it: maybe some grilled chicken or even serve it alongside grilled filet. Make it your caesar of the summer, you know? \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI’ve made \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2014/02/warm-brussels-caesar-with-bacon-ciabatta-croutons/\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ebrussels caesar\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2021/03/grilled-asparagus-caesar-salad/\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003easparagus caesar\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e and I think that a green bean caesar might be next. I’m all about \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2023/05/caesar-pasta-salad/\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003emy caesar pasta salad\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e too. That flavor and texture is so wonderful!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"grilled zucchini caesar\" width=\"1711\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Zucchini Caesar.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-scaled.jpg 1711w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-728x936.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-768x988.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-1194x1536.jpg 1194w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-1593x2048.jpg 1593w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-150x193.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1711px) 100vw, 1711px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201711%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-scaled.jpg 1711w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-728x936.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-768x988.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-1194x1536.jpg 1194w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-1593x2048.jpg 1593w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-150x193.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-4-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSince zucchini is on the softer side, I was afraid that this would not have enough texture for me. Hence – the sourdough breadcrumbs.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThey add so much flavor AND texture. I’m all about the crispy crunch and this is exactly what the dish requires. Without the crumbs, you’re just going to have soft grilled zucchini with a dressing. And cheese. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eNot that I’d ever complain about dressing and cheese, but you know! \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"grilled zucchini caesar\" width=\"1817\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Zucchini Caesar.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-scaled.jpg 1817w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-728x881.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-768x930.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-1269x1536.jpg 1269w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-1692x2048.jpg 1692w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-150x182.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1817px) 100vw, 1817px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201817%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-scaled.jpg 1817w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-728x881.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-768x930.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-1269x1536.jpg 1269w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-1692x2048.jpg 1692w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-150x182.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-6-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eLet’s talk about the grill. \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/44j7FRs\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThis is my favorite grill pan\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e and it has been for years. It has held up so well – \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/44j7FRs\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI have two of them\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e because sometimes I grill a TON of vegetables. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTo make this, I cut the zucchini into large chunks and grill it right on the pan. I am really familiar with my grill though. Another option is to slice the zucchini in half and grill the large pieces, then once they are charred and cooled, chop them into chunks. Both methods work! \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"grilled zucchini caesar\" width=\"1806\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Zucchini Caesar.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-scaled.jpg 1806w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-728x887.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-768x935.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-1261x1536.jpg 1261w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-1681x2048.jpg 1681w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-150x183.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1806px) 100vw, 1806px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201806%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-scaled.jpg 1806w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-728x887.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-768x935.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-1261x1536.jpg 1261w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-1681x2048.jpg 1681w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-150x183.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-8-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI rarely serve this warm. It’s often either room temperature or almost chilled thanks to the dressing. I love it that way and it’s perfect. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eBoth a mixture of shaved parm and finely grated parmesan are key here: there is so much flavor with each bite and different textures of the cheese is what makes it special. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan id=\"more-100037\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"grilled zucchini caesar\" width=\"1695\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Zucchini Caesar.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-scaled.jpg 1695w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-728x945.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-768x997.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-1184x1536.jpg 1184w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-1578x2048.jpg 1578w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-150x195.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1695px) 100vw, 1695px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201695%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-scaled.jpg 1695w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-728x945.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-768x997.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-1184x1536.jpg 1184w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-1578x2048.jpg 1578w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-150x195.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-13-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAnd then of course, the breadcrumbs! After you toast them, make sure to crush them with your hand so they get into super tiny crunchy pieces. Yesssss. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"grilled zucchini caesar\" width=\"1879\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Zucchini Caesar.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-scaled.jpg 1879w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-728x852.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-768x899.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-1312x1536.jpg 1312w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-1749x2048.jpg 1749w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-150x176.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1879px) 100vw, 1879px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201879%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-scaled.jpg 1879w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-728x852.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-768x899.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-1312x1536.jpg 1312w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-1749x2048.jpg 1749w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-150x176.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-14-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eGrilled Zucchini Caesar\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv id=\"wprm-recipe-container-100054\" data-recipe-id=\"100054\" data-servings=\"2\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-250x250.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-250x250.jpg 250w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-500x500.jpg 500w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-336x336.jpg 336w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-672x672.jpg 672w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-96x96.jpg 96w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%20200%20200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-250x250.jpg 250w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-500x500.jpg 500w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-336x336.jpg 336w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-672x672.jpg 672w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-300x300.jpg 300w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-96x96.jpg 96w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-9-250x250.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eGrilled Zucchini Caesar\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" x=\"0px\" y=\"0px\" width=\"16px\" height=\"16px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"\u003e\u003cg\u003e\u003cpath fill=\"#ae0481\" d=\"M10,0C9.4,0,9,0.4,9,1v4H7V1c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1S5,0.4,5,1v4H3V1c0-0.6-0.4-1-1-1S1,0.4,1,1v8c0,1.7,1.3,3,3,3v10c0,1.1,0.9,2,2,2s2-0.9,2-2V12c1.7,0,3-1.3,3-3V1C11,0.4,10.6,0,10,0z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003cpath data-color=\"color-2\" fill=\"#ae0481\" d=\"M19,0c-3.3,0-6,2.7-6,6v9c0,0.6,0.4,1,1,1h2v6c0,1.1,0.9,2,2,2s2-0.9,2-2V1C20,0.4,19.6,0,19,0z\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/g\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003eYield: \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan data-recipe=\"100054\" aria-label=\"Adjust recipe servings\"\u003e2\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003eto 4\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePrep Time: \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e20\u003cspan\u003e minutes\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCook Time: \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e15\u003cspan\u003e minutes\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eTotal Time: \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e35\u003cspan\u003e minutes\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\t\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOh how I love this grilled zucchini caesar! Big chunks of zucchini, charred and caramelized on the grill, drizzled with greek yogurt caesar dressing and topped with shaved parmesan and crunchy breadcrumbs. Delicious summer meal!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"recipe-100054-ingredients\" data-recipe=\"100054\" data-servings=\"2\"\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"0\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e2 to 3\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.target.com/p/organic-zucchini-2ct/-/A-85825253?aflt=plt#lnk=sametab\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003emedium zucchini,\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003ecut into chunks\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"1\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ekosher salt and pepper\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"2\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e3\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003eslices\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003esourdough bread,\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003ecut into cubes\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"3\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e2\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003etablespoons\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.target.com/p/land-o-lakes-unsalted-butter-1lb/-/A-13227053?aflt=plt\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eunsalted butter\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"4\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e2\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.target.com/p/spice-world-fresh-whole-garlic-3ct-bag/-/A-14917318?aflt=plt\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003egarlic cloves,\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003eminced\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"5\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003etablespoon\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.target.com/p/pure-olive-oil-25-5oz-good-38-gather-8482/-/A-77600361?aflt=plt#lnk=sametab\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eolive oil\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"6\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e⅓\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003ecup\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003eshaved parmesan cheese\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli data-uid=\"7\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e2\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003etablespoons\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.target.com/p/kraft-100-grated-parmesan-cheese-8oz/-/A-12958582?aflt=plt#lnk=sametab\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003efinely grated parmesan cheese\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"recipe-100054-instructions\" data-recipe=\"100054\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-100054-step-0-0\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eCut the zucchini into chunks. Place the chunks on a few layers of paper towels and sprinkle them with salt. This will remove the moisture so the zucchini doesn’t get mushy on the grill. Let it sit for 15 to 20 minutes.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-100054-step-0-1\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eMake the bread crumbs while the zucchini sits. Heat a skillet over medium heat and add the butter. Add in the torn sourdough pieces with a pinch of salt and pepper along with the garlic cloves. Cook, tossing often, until the bread is crunchy and golden, about 5 to 6 minutes. Transfer it to a plate and let it cool. Once cool, crumble the pieces even further with your hands.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-100054-step-0-2\"\u003e\u003cp\u003ePreheat your grill to the highest setting. Pat the zucchini dry with the paper towels all over and place the chunks in a bowl. Toss with the olive oil and a big pinch of pepper (they are already salted). Transfer the zucchini to a grill pan.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-100054-step-0-3\"\u003e\u003cp\u003ePlace the pan on the grill and close the lid. Grill for 6 to 8 minutes, then toss and grill for 6 to 8 minutes more. Grill from anywhere for 5 to 10 more minutes, or until they are grilled enough for your liking. Remove the grill pan.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-100054-step-0-4\"\u003e\u003cp\u003ePlace the zucchini on a large plate. Drizzle with a few spoonfuls of the caesar dressing. Top with the shaved parmesan and grated parmesan. Top with the breadcrumbs. Enjoy!\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch4\u003egreek yogurt caesar dressing\u003c/h4\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli id=\"wprm-recipe-100054-step-1-0\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eAdd the garlic, yogurt, parmesan, mustard, vinegar, anchovy paste, lemon juice, a pinch of salt and pepper to a food processor or blender and blend until pureed. With the processor still on, stream in the olive oil until a creamy dressing forms. (This may make more dressing than needed, but you can store it sealed in the fridge for about 3 to 4 days and stir well before using.)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCourse: \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eSide Dish\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eCuisine: \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAmerican\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"grilled zucchini caesar\" width=\"1765\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Zucchini Caesar.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-scaled.jpg 1765w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-728x907.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-768x957.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-1232x1536.jpg 1232w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-1643x2048.jpg 1643w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-150x187.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1765px) 100vw, 1765px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201765%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-scaled.jpg 1765w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-728x907.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-768x957.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-1232x1536.jpg 1232w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-1643x2048.jpg 1643w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-150x187.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/grilled-zucchini-caesar-16-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCaramelized crunchy goodness.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\n\t\t\n\u003c/article\u003e \n\n\t\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\t\n\n\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
